  <discussion>Pogonatum brachyphyllum is endemic to eastern North America, and it has a more southerly distribution than P. pensilvanicum.  The leaves of P. brachyphyllum are entire, short and broad, and appear succulent because of tall, closely packed lamellae.  The calyptra is yellowish to reddish brown, contrasting with the rich, green protonemal mat.</discussion>
